  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they tried to explain to me that being a Jew at that-- at that time was different, and that there was-- as much as they could explain anti-Semitism to me-- that the parents of my friends are probably the ones that were suggesting no association with me at that time, because then the Germans had already come in.",
      "word_count": 59
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they began-- And I think that the anti-Semitism that they had, which was, I think, restrained at that point, really came out.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And you saw what their true feelings were.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "As I said, my first recollection of anti-Semitism, or coming across that, was my friends no longer wanting to play with me.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not quite.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It took a lot more than that.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It took many of the things that I finally got to see on the streets of Belgium.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Germans dragging-- well, at the time, of course, we had finally been made to wear the Jewish star.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Which of course made [INAUDIBLE] I started to understand how different we were, that we were made to wear a yellow star with a J on it, and my friends that weren't Jewish did not.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then I started seeing some arresting and deportation and beating and things of that sort, and all the time asking why.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And every time, it was pounded into me that only because we were Jewish, and we had to be careful.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we had to be very careful about who we associated with.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then it started to be explained to me about uniforms and Germans.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And the thing that I thought was a very exciting thing happening in Belgium-- I didn't quite understand the word invasion at the time-- started to hit home, that these people were to be feared, that they didn't like Jews.",
      "word_count": 40
    }
  ],
